Dialogs.Dialog: What do you plan to do on New Year's？
Manaka
I'll rest on New Year's Day. But after that, I'll be busy going around and greeting people.
I see. Do you have to visit many people？
Not that many, but it's still very tiresome.
Why？
I have to make desserts for New Year's gifts every year. I'm quite worried about that...
Every year？ Can't you just stop doing that？
My parents said I didn't have to do it, but I just don't want to quit.
It would be like losing if I quit, right...？
(Even in a situation like this, she's still competitive...)
Setsubun is in February. What do you do at home, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
We decorate our home with the evil buster charm and scatter beans to drive evil away.
The evil buster charm？
You don't know what it is？ It's made with holly olive and pilchard's head.
Papa always takes care of scattering the beans. Mama and I just do the cleaning later.
Who takes the demon role then？
No one. It's like we exorcise the invisible evil spirits.
After it's done, we just have some good luck tea. It's delicious. Hehe, I can't wait.
(They have such an elegant Setsubun tradition...)
It's almost that time of year again. Valentine's Day！
Manaka
...Are you concerned about it？
Well yeah, because I have a girlfriend who's very good at cooking！
Come on... But, don't expect too much, okay？
Eh？ This is rare. Cooking is your specialty, isn't it？
Yeah... But I couldn't find the topping I intended to use. It's sold out everywhere.
Ah... I'll have to find a substitute for it.
(Even good cooks encounter such tough situations, huh...？)
Hey, it's almost that time of year again, right？ Valentine's Day！
Manaka
Yes. Right now, I have so many choices that I really can't decide.
So, if you have any requests, maybe you should tell me... I'm kidding.
▲高嶺＊＊▲, you can make whatever you want. Anything is okay for me！ I'll leave it to you.
Hehe！ Somehow, that's what I expected you to say.
I'll try my best to make something that will make you happy.
(Ah, I can't wait！)
Hey, it's almost that time of year again, right？ Valentine's Day！
Manaka
Are you expecting for something？
Of course！
...I have to apologize first. I'm sorry.
Eh！？ W-Why？
It might be so delicious that your jaw will drop▼
Hehe！
(Hah. What a surprise... But now I can't wait！)
Hinamatsuri is coming up soon. Do you have doll decorations at your house, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Yes, of course. We have them up for the whole month of February.
You put them up that early？
Yeah. We put them up early and then put them away as soon as the festival ends. It's our tradition.
I see. But why？ They are so pretty. It would be better to display them longer.
Hmm？
Maybe I should leave them on a little longer... Hehe.
By the way, it's almost White Day...
Manaka
Yeah.
Eh？ Don't tell me you don't expect anything at all.
I'm expecting something. But it's not like I want anything luxurious in return, so don't worry.
But, if I had to say...
I'm expecting something packed with your feelings.
Hehe. Do your best and think about it, okay？
(All right. I'll do my best！)
To think of it... It's almost a month after Valentine's Day.
Manaka
White Day's coming, right？
Do you have anything you want in particular？
No. Just your feelings are more than enough.
WReally. Anything is fine. For me, everything you give me is always a precious treasure.
(Ah！ She's saying it in such a cute way. It makes me want to do my best for her！)
It's been almost a month since Valentine's Day, huh？
Manaka
Yeah▼
Eh...？ Are you anticipating something big because of me？
Hehe.
More than anticipation... Right now, you must be thinking a lot about the return gift, right？
Yeah.
T-That means you're thinking about me all the time, right？ I'm so happy.
I wonder what kind of gift you'll choose for me. I'm anticipating that.
I can't wait▼
(All right. I'll do my best choosing a gift for her！)
It's the cherry blossom season.
Manaka
Yeah. When I was a kid, I often went to see weeping cherry blossom trees.
How were they？
They were so big and pretty. I felt like I was walking under raining petals.
Hmm... I want to see them too.
But those trees are located very far from here. We can't go there in a one-day trip.
I see...
But we'll go to see them together, okay？ Maybe when we grow up. Let's promise.
It's almost Golden Week. ▲高嶺＊＊▲, do you want to go somewhere？
Manaka
It's going to be crowded everywhere, isn't it？ It's okay if I can just hang out with you at home...
You're like a worn-out salaryman！
How's my joke？
...I won't go anywhere with you. I won't even let you in my house！
(Eh！？ Why？)
It's almost the sports festival. Are you going to participate in any events, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Yes, many of them.
As I thought... ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is good at everything.
Hey, if I win in a lot of events, will you give me a reward？
Oh, of course I will！
Yay▼ I'll do my best. Maybe I can win all of them.
(Then I'll have to do my best, too！)
By the way, it's time to change uniforms again.
Manaka
I prefer the winter uniform.
Really？ Why？ Isn't the summer uniform nice？
I don't want to get sunburnt.
Ah, that's the reason...
I can never understand why guys are so happy when girls dress so lightly.
Um... That's... Well...
...Geez. Never ever look at other girls like that with those eyes, okay？
(I'll be careful...)
It's July now... What do you plan to wish for on Tanabata？
Manaka
My family set up a bamboo decoration at home, so I'll hang my wish card there.
Wow. ▲高嶺＊＊▲'s family celebrates almost every festival, eh？
Yeah, pretty much. My family just likes things like this.
I heard that they didn't do this much to begin with, but started to after I was born.
I'm a girl, but they celebrate Boys' Festival by hanging carp streamers too. Next is the Moon Festival, I think...
Wow, they really celebrate them all... Oh, about your wish, what will you wish for？
That's... To be with you... Never mind. It's my secret.
Ah！ Can't summer break come any faster！？
Manaka
Why？
Eh？ Aren't you looking forward to it？
Well, not really. During the holidays, it's more difficult for us to meet every day.
Yeah, that's true... But we can always hang out together outside, too.
...That's right. Yeah, I'm also looking forward to it then.
Good！ I can't wait to go to lots of seasonal events with you. I want to see you in a swimsuit and in a yukata too.
So those are all you're looking forward to？
Boo, not just those. A lot more！ We're gonna have a busy summer, so be prepared, ▲高嶺＊＊▲.
Yes~▼
(Let's have fun！)
It's almost sea bathing season, right？
Manaka
Yeah... Swimsuits, huh...
You aren't confident？ I'm sure you'll look good in any swimsuit, bikini or tankini. Don't worry about it！
I don't know which one I should wear... Can I consult you？
Of course！
Great. I'll trouble you for that.
(But if you wear a school swimsuit, I'll be angry, you know...？)
It's almost fireworks season... Have you bought your yukata？
Manaka
Hehe, I did. You can look forward to it, okay？
By the way, can you put on a yukata by yourself, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Yes. If you remember the order, it's quite simple.
It's just that having to wear a yukata with a tight sash is quite irritating in the summer.
Hmm？ Then if you can't stand it, I can help you untie the sash. It'll make you feel better...
...Huh？ N-No！ I didn't mean it that way！ I said it with innocent intentions...！
I don't care.
(Ahhhhh~)
Ah... Summer is ending soon.
Manaka
What？ Why are you sighing？
I like school days more. I can see you more often than during the break...
Yeah... But, still...
Ah, I know. You haven't finished your homework, right？
Yeah, that's one reason, too...
Geez, what a helpless guy. Come on. I'll help you, so cheer up, okay？
(Yay！ ...But I still don't want summer break to end...)
It's almost the Harvest Moon.
Manaka
Yeah, I already prepared some pampas grass. Later, I'll only have to prepare the offerings.
So you're the one in charge of the offerings, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Well, every year, Mama and I make sweet dumplings together.
How about your father？
He joins us too. I think he kind of likes it. He's like a kid sometimes.
Hahaha. That's good. I want to join in, too.
It'd be nice if you become a part of my family...
Right！ ...What！？
Hehe！
It's time to change our uniforms again.
Manaka
Yeah. I really like the winter uniform.
Um, you look good in it.
...Even if you try to flatter me, I don't have anything for you.
It's not flattery and I don't want anything♪
...Hey. You're just making fun of me.
▲高嶺＊＊▲. Your face is all red. So cute.
...I don't care！
(Really. It's nice that ▲高嶺＊＊▲ gets shy easily like this.)
It's almost the culture festival.
Manaka
Yeah. Everyone is so excited about it. I wonder if we can get all the preparation done in time.
Who knows.
Hehe. I guess so. Hey, you'll have some free time, right？
Of course！ Let's go around the festival together. We can go to the haunted house, and then the haunted house.
Fine... But why did you mention it twice？
Ah, no... I just thought that it would be good to go to the haunted house...
...Too bad.
I'm quite cool with it. I won't get scared. If you've planned something, it's probably useless.
(...Is it true or is she just bluffing？)
It's almost skiing season.
Manaka
Ski...
Are you bad at skiing？
Yeah... I'm not good. I keep falling down all the time.
▲高嶺＊＊▲ also has some weak points too, huh？
Of course. No one is flawless.
No, I didn't mean I want you to be flawless. It's just that I'm happy to learn more about you.
Ah...
...I'm sorry. If we go skiing, will you teach me then？
Of course！
It's almost Christmas...
Manaka
Yes. I like the atmosphere like this. Every place looks sparkling and everyone is so happy...
Yeah, you're right.
And being able to be with you makes me like it even more.
Yeah, me too.
Hehe. I can't wait for Christmas.
(I'll try to make Christmas this year a nice one for her.)
It's almost Christmas. You said before that you'd have a party at your house, right, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Manaka
Yeah. But the party will start very late this year, so it's fine.
Why？
...I just tried my best, that's why.
Never mind！ I can't wait for Christmas.
(I'll try to make Christmas this year a nice one for her.)
It's almost Christmas...
Manaka
Yes. Last time, I said that I loved the atmosphere, right？ This is just so amazing.
When I have you by my side, I feel like I'm a heroine.
So now, I'm your prince, and ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is my princess, okay？
Hehe. Will you take me to the party by a carriage with white horses？
(I'll try to make Christmas this year a nice one for her.)
KIt's almost the end of the year... A lot of things happened this year, huh？
Manaka
Yeah... Right.
▲高嶺＊＊▲. What was the most memorable thing for you？
That's... Of course, it's that thing...
Our first date？
Our first kiss？
What is it？
It must be our first date, right？ It became the big news of the year.
Yes. I still can't believe it even now.
Huh？ What？
That you and I are talking to each other like this. Just a while ago, we were still just friends...
I'm very grateful to God for giving me this chance. ...Please continue to treat me well.
Likewise！
It must be... our first kiss, right？
...Yeah. People say that first kiss is something special. And it really is.
For me too... Huh？ What's wrong？
...Don't look. When I think of it, I feel really embarrassed...
(It only happens once in our lifetime. Now even I feel embarrassed...)
Huh？ What is it？
It's... Hey...
...Look at you. You knew it, right？
I really don't know.
Enough already... You're just so stupid.
(You don't have to say that...)
It's the end of the year. Many things have happened, eh？
Manaka
Yeah. Please be nice to me next year too, okay？
Likewise！
...Hehe.
Huh？ What？
Somehow, I feel like we might just repeat this conversation next year too.
Haha. I guess so. Maybe we should talk about our plans for the next New Year's.
I agree. So, let's think about it.
(Um, it's very nice like this.)
It's almost spring.
Manaka
We'll start to smell the flower's fragrances in the wind, right？
And then the grocers will go out to find bamboo shoots and stuff.
Yeah, it's this time of year. Such a nice season.
Right. It's also fun to think about menus to match the seasons.
Maybe I'll try cooking a bamboo shoot dish later.
(Sounds nice. Ah, now I'm getting hungry...)
It's getting warmer now.
Manaka
Hehe. The feeling of spring, eh？
Ah, right. I have to buy some strawberries on the way home.
▲高嶺＊＊▲, do you like strawberries？
Love them▼ I can make jam, or fluffy mousse, or a lot more. I can eat them all.
It's called "strawberry hell" at the Takanes during this season. Hehe▼
(Isn't it supposed to be "heaven"？ Somehow, this sounds scary...)
The days seems to be longer now. Summer is coming soon, I guess.
Manaka
Ah...
Eh？ You don't like summer？
No, that's not the case, but... I have to deal with sunburns.
When I get sunburnt, my whole body becomes red.
I see. It's not easy to be a girl.
That's right. I have to plan ahead on how to avoid getting burned.
But I'm a bit jealous of others. I want to get tanned skin, too.
(And somehow, I want to see that.)
It's summer already... It's hot. Too hot.
Manaka
Do you want to be in an air-conditioned room all day？ That's not good for your health.
Huh？ So, you don't have air conditioning at home, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
I do, but I only use it at night. I don't quite like it.
How about an electric fan？
I like it. I like to say "Aaaaa" in front of it.
"Waa ree waa ree waaaa" like this. I do this every year.
(I bet I'm the only one who knows she does something like that！)
Lately, the sky has become higher.
Manaka
The clouds are also changing their shapes. It's almost fall, right？
Yeah. By the way, what do you like most in fall, ▲高嶺＊＊▲？
Hehe. What I like most？ I like music, I guess. Fall is the best time to listen or to play the piano.
You chose music, not food, eh？
Hey, don't make me look like a glutton...
Eh？ You aren't？
...Anyway, I'm just a moderate glutton.
(Which part is moderate！？)
It's getting dark quite early. It's fall already, eh？
Manaka
It's a peaceful season. Food is delicious during this season too. So nice.
Fall makes me think of eggplants, mushrooms, pikes, potatoes...
Don't forget pears, grapes, ginkgos, persimmons, and chestnuts▼
Fall, the season for eating. Hooray！
Hehe. So you've become a glutton now, right？
(I'm a glutton, eh？)
It's getting cold.
Manaka
Will it get colder？ If it does, I'll have to wear my coat.
▲高嶺＊＊▲, are you okay with cold weather？
Yeah, relatively okay.
It's different from hot weather. As long as I'm wearing enough clothes, I can stay warm.
Sometimes I keep wearing coat in the house and my parents are like "Just turn on the heat！" Hehe！
(So, ▲高嶺＊＊▲ is quite concerned about energy conservation, eh？)
Urgh, so cold... As I expected of winter.
Manaka
It'd be good if we could eat hot pot every day to keep ourselves warm.
Yeah. And then get under a kotatsu table and eat some oranges.
Or you can have some ice cream too.
Nah, thinking about the season, oranges are way better.
！！ Urgh...
(What was that just now...？)
